O, our Teddy, he's a wonder when
it comes to being brave;
He has camped before the en-
trance of the mountain lion's
cave;
He has dallied with the wild-
cat, he has wrestted with the bear;
And explored the ocean's bot-
tom, scoffing at the dangers there;
He has bravely led in battle
where the air was full of lead;
But I wonder if he ever dared
to try the folding bed.—Ex.
